{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<div class=\"work_section overview col_full\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <p>\n      When Facebook went on a month-long &quot;lockdown&quot; in early 2016 to ship Live\n      Videos on its platform, I oversaw the product design and direction of a\n      new reporting flow empowering people to report objectionable, sensitive\n      content from Live Videos. I conceived, coordinated, designed, executed,\n      and ship a product resulting in higher report volumes of objectionable\n      content that our Community Operations organization was able to remove\n      (with a 39.7% form completion compared to 3.11% previously). This\n      enables Facebook to become a safer platform for people to be their\n      authentic selves.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section no_margin col_full_stretch\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <figure>\n      \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/3a11c/project_overview.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.825795644891116%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"project overview\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/c83f1/project_overview.png\" srcset=\"/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/569e3/project_overview.png 240w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/93400/project_overview.png 480w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/c83f1/project_overview.png 960w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/23e13/project_overview.png 1440w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/10d8f/project_overview.png 1920w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/6bb82/project_overview.png 2880w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/3a11c/project_overview.png 4776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n    </figure>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section col_full\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <h5 class=\"work_section_title\">\n      Objective\n    </h5>\n    <h2>\n      Empower people to report live videos showing offensive or flagrant\n      content, such as graphic violence, hate speech, nudity and pornography,\n      spam, and more.\n    </h2>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section col_full\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <h5 class=\"work_section_title\">\n      Background\n    </h5>\n    <p>\n      Up until this project, I had been investigating how to improve Facebook&apos;s\nexisting reporting flow so that people can better flag objectionable content\nanywhere from Facebook. The existing reporting flow wasn&apos;t efficient nor ideal\nin meeting users&apos; needs. Furthermore, it was built on a legacy code base\nconstrained making meaningful iterative design and engineering changes.\nFurthermore, it was a product that many cross-functional teams had much stake\nand voice in, such as the Policy, Communications, and Community Operations\nteams.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      Through ample user research, our team highlighted that these were the\n      core needs and expectations that people have been they encounter a\n      problem on Facebook. Our responsibility was to meet people where they are\n      at.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section col_mid_stretch align_center mg_dw_m\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <div class=\"list_container_col\">\n      <article class=\"list_item\">\n        <div class=\"list_counter\">\n          <h5 class=\"list_counter_value\">\n            01\n          </h5>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"list_content\">\n          <h4 class=\"list_content_title\">\n            Discover\n          </h4>\n          <p class=\"list_content_description\">\n            People know where and how to report content on Facebook.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"list_item\">\n        <div class=\"list_counter\">\n          <h5 class=\"list_counter_value\">\n            02\n          </h5>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"list_content\">\n          <h4 class=\"list_content_title\">\n            Express\n          </h4>\n          <p class=\"list_content_description\">\n            People can express and articulate what their issue is.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"list_item\">\n        <div class=\"list_counter\">\n          <h5 class=\"list_counter_value\">\n            03\n          </h5>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"list_content\">\n          <h4 class=\"list_content_title\">\n            Take Action\n          </h4>\n          <p class=\"list_content_description\">\n            People know that they can take action to resolve their problem.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"list_item\">\n        <div class=\"list_counter\">\n          <h5 class=\"list_counter_value\">\n            04\n          </h5>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"list_content\">\n          <h4 class=\"list_content_title\">\n            Confirmation\n          </h4>\n          <p class=\"list_content_description\">\n            People know that their issue is being taken care of.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section no_margin highlight col_full_stretch\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <div class=\"ctr col_ctr\">\n      <h2>\n        What was wrong with the existing reporting flow?\n      </h2>\n      <p>\n        The legacy reporting system was filled with many UX and UI problems\n        that made it challenging for people to discover, express their problem,\n        and see the help they needed.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n    <hr>\n    <figure>\n      \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/dbb47/existing_flow.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 46.17534942820839%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"existing flow\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/c83f1/existing_flow.png\" srcset=\"/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/569e3/existing_flow.png 240w,\n/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/93400/existing_flow.png 480w,\n/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/c83f1/existing_flow.png 960w,\n/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/23e13/existing_flow.png 1440w,\n/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/10d8f/existing_flow.png 1920w,\n/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/6bb82/existing_flow.png 2880w,\n/static/bd795568dc5e38c8502f4a1ee1f62de5/dbb47/existing_flow.png 7870w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n    </figure>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section col_full\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <h2>\n      The opportunity\n    </h2>\n    <p>\n      When Mark Zuckerberg announced internally that the company would focus\n      deeply on Live Videos for a month-long sprint, my team joined its\n      efforts. Rather than adapt the existing reporting flow to Live Videos, we\n      built a new one from scratch. I worked rapidly across multiple time zones\n      with stakeholders in Product, Policy, and Community Operations to\n      understand our requirements, unblock constraints and unknowns, and drive\n      alignment to ship an improved reporting flow. This new reporting flow made\n      it easier for people to discover, express their problem, and find the\n      help that they need from Facebook.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      Improvements in the new reporting flow introduced new principles to bring\n      into our reporting system overall:\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section no_margin highlight col_mid_stretch mg_dw_m\">\n  <div class=\"col fl fl_ai_ctr\">\n    <div class=\"col_2of3 pd_rt_s\">\n      <h2>\n        Richer Expression\n      </h2>\n      <p>\n        <strong>\n          How might we help people better express their issues on our\n          platform?\n        </strong>\n        The new reporting form relies on tags and open-textfield for user\n        input. This made it possible for people to select multiple tags,\n        allowing fuller expression of their problem. They could also now\n        describe their issues in in their own words.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"col_1of3\">\n      <figure>\n        \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/14179/expression.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 173.23759791122717%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"expression\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/c83f1/expression.png\" srcset=\"/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/569e3/expression.png 240w,\n/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/93400/expression.png 480w,\n/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/c83f1/expression.png 960w,\n/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/23e13/expression.png 1440w,\n/static/33cd424c23bf79c8e142bedaa50ace8d/14179/expression.png 1532w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n      </figure>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <hr>\n  <div class=\"col fl fl_ai_ctr\">\n    <div class=\"col_1of3\">\n      <figure>\n        \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/14179/ssi.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 173.23759791122717%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"ssi\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/c83f1/ssi.png\" srcset=\"/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/569e3/ssi.png 240w,\n/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/93400/ssi.png 480w,\n/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/c83f1/ssi.png 960w,\n/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/23e13/ssi.png 1440w,\n/static/0c08f5b5c18837f845d57d90cf5e90d3/14179/ssi.png 1532w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n      </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"col_2of3 pd_lf_s\">\n      <h2>\n        Dynamic and Personalized\n      </h2>\n      <p>\n        <strong>\n          How might we better affirm we&apos;re listening to your issues?\n        </strong>\n        Amidst the wide range of issues that people can select, we recognize\n        that suicide and self-injury are immediate emergencies require instant\n        aid. That&apos;s why we ask people to contact their law enforcements, who\n        are most equipped to handle the situation in real-time.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <hr>\n  <div class=\"col fl fl_ai_ctr\">\n    <div class=\"col_2of3 pd_rt_s\">\n      <h2>\n        Clearer Confirmation\n      </h2>\n      <p>\n        <strong>\n          How might we give people clear expectations of what&apos;s next?\n        </strong>\n        Whereas the previous reporting flow did not give people confidence that\n        they submitted a report, this one clarifies it better through\n        iconography, typographic hierarchy, and content.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"col_1of3\">\n      <figure>\n        \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/14179/confirmation.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 173.23759791122717%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"confirmation\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/c83f1/confirmation.png\" srcset=\"/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/569e3/confirmation.png 240w,\n/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/93400/confirmation.png 480w,\n/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/c83f1/confirmation.png 960w,\n/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/23e13/confirmation.png 1440w,\n/static/e85a83790dac1e6db37a01bacc9c37ba/14179/confirmation.png 1532w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n      </figure>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section col_full\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <h2>\n      Outcomes\n    </h2>\n    <p>\n      The Live Video reporting flow was more effective in flagging flagrant\n      content than the existing reporting flow. When we A/B launched the two\n      flows, we found that the new reporting flow captured:\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      </p><ul class=\"styled\">\n        <li>\n          1.5x more policy-violating Live broadcasts.\n        </li>\n        <li>\n          7.5x more distinct people reporting Live\n          broadcasts.\n        </li>\n        <li>\n          5.75x more distinct Live broadcasts reviewable by our Community\n          Operations team.\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n    <p></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"work_section no_margin col_full_stretch\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <figure>\n      \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/3a11c/project_overview.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.825795644891116%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"project overview\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/c83f1/project_overview.png\" srcset=\"/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/569e3/project_overview.png 240w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/93400/project_overview.png 480w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/c83f1/project_overview.png 960w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/23e13/project_overview.png 1440w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/10d8f/project_overview.png 1920w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/6bb82/project_overview.png 2880w,\n/static/5edce5c6480e4127073ea74aabea37e4/3a11c/project_overview.png 4776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n    </figure>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"work_section col_full\">\n  <div class=\"col\">\n    <h2>\n      Recap\n    </h2>\n    <p class=\"special_paragraph\">\n      This project was exciting and allowed our team to move fast with the validation we had already heard from our data and user research. I approached the project with these principles in mind:\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      </p><ul class=\"styled\">\n        <li>\n          <strong>\n            Collaboration\n          </strong>\n          <br>\n          Drove end-to-end design and development across multiple internal\n          organizations (Product, Policy, Communications, Community Operations)\n           with colleagues in Menlo Park, Seattle, and London.\n        </li>\n        <li>\n          <strong>\n            Agile\n          </strong>\n          <br>\n          Coordinated agilely with core Live Videos team to develop a\n          consistent product experience in tandem with each other.\n        </li>\n        <li>\n          <strong>\n            Extensibility\n          </strong>\n          <br>\n          Developed an extensible product framework applicable to varying\n          severity of reporting use cases, ranging from most &quot;minor&quot; (nudity or\n          sex acts) to most critical (suicide and self-injury).\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n    <p></p>\n  </div>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Reporting Sensitive Live Videos","duration":"2016","role":"Product Design Lead","subtitle":"Designed and launched the reporting flow on Facebook's Live Videos globally on all platforms, ensuring that people can report any violating content they see.","reference":"fb_live_reporting","featured_image":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"src":"/static/d211af17dd6db1154aaed0083bd9d9bf/6d47d/header_bg.png"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/works/fb_live_reporting/"}}